This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during the National Teacher of the Year celebration at the White House. The President thanked Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos and Secretary of Labor Alex Acosta for attending the event. He also acknowledged the Walter B. Patterson Elementary School Glee Club for their performance. The President congratulated the Teachers of the Year from each state, territory, and the District of Columbia. He introduced the three finalists for National Teacher of the Year, Amy Anderson, Jonathan Juravich, and Kara Ball. The President expressed his admiration for the dedication of teachers and the importance of their role in shaping the future generation. He then announced Mandy Manning from Washington as the recipient of the National Teacher of the Year award. The President presented her with the award and concluded his remarks by thanking everyone for attending and wishing them the best.